            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">You know what boggles my mind?  I heard that post napster (before it was nuked), CD sales were the highest they have ever been.  <br />
<br />
People who buy CD's regularily - for the most part - still buy CD's regularily.  People whom don't normally buy CD's (me), start to download music from napster or kazaa or morpheus or porndigg... i mean... ehem.   <br />
<br />
Anyway, those people think "Wow, these are good musics, I thunk I aughta buy me some of dem CD critters I always see at best buy."  People who are inspired to buy music they hear on napster far outweigh those who stop buying music to burn the CD's.  Most of those who burn usually didn't buy CD's anyway.</font></p>
             
