            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1"><blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1">quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Ralkora </i><br />
<b><br />
Well shit, I'd be happy just being famous.  Greedy bastards. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""> (Hey thats all I aim for.. i dont care so much bout the cash, i just enjoy what i do.. ok being famous would be cool.. but.. lol)<br />
</b><hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
I know what you mean.  When I write (or used to, it seems), I did it for the enjoyment.  That's why I haven't written in a while, because I don't force myself to if I'm not in the mood.  I'm not trying to get rich off any of my stuff.  It would be nice to make a little something, but what I really aim for is is to wreck peoples emotions, so that they feel it all over.  The biggest reward from my stuff is when I get a letter or email from someone saying how much they enjoyed my work, because when they take the time to write you a letter, it was more than just "good" to them.  Or when they tell me that they finally think they know what I was trying to say, because a lot of my stuff is like Reapin's picture.  To look at it you're like, "WTF?", but you've got to dig.<br />
<br />
Anyway, I'm getting off topic here.  My point is, I've had several pieces of my written work published, and a piece of composition was used on a compilation CD two or three years ago.  I don't know if any of it is floating around on a P2P network, because I've never looked, but I hope it is.  Like I said, money would be nice, but having more people read and enjoy it is more important to me.<br />
<br />
I don't use P2P much, once every few months, but I have no pity for the recording artists, or the music industry.  Keep in mind, that several of my close friends are in a few bands that are very close to breaking through the top.  I wish them the best, but that doesn't change my opinion.  These people are getting paid to sit around and have fun all day, just like professional athletes.  I wish I got paid 50k/year to do something I enjoyed that much....  They don't need millions of dollars to do this stuff, so when they start crying about loss of income, I laugh.  When I see "stars" filing for Ch. 11, I crap my pants.  Anyone that can take $30+ and lose it that fast, deserves exactly what they got.</font></p>
             
