             </font> 
            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">I do agree to the point that it hurts the music industry, yes, but I'd rather go for it scratches the surface. The Real deal the industry makes is with the professional DJs, clubs and radio. They make Music Compilations that sell very well too. Private Single CD buying is still a part of it, but how many of the people who download music completely knock off buying CDs?<br />
In the end, in my opinion, they are making a big fuss for a minimal percentage lost. I yet have to find statistics though...</font></p>
             
