            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">Exactly.  They say CD sales are down 25% from '99, but how much of that has to do with pirating, and how much has to do with CD costs, shitty music, change of interest, etc?  What would the decline have been if there were no P2P networks?  I'd say close to the same, because I know many people stopped buying CDs for the reasons I just stated.<br />
<br />
They're just looking for someone to point a finger at, and hoping to make a few extra bucks from it.</font></p>
             
